# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# .dockerignore — build-context filter for the forge production image
# (TASK-F009-002, AC-F).
#
# Goals:
#   * Keep the build context small (a fast `docker build` on a slow
#     network depends on this).
#   * Prevent host-side state from leaking into the image — VCS history,
#     local virtualenvs, .guardkit autobuild scratch, .env secrets.
#   * Avoid invalidating the build cache when only tests, docs, or
#     task-tracking files change.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Version control & local-only worktrees.
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.guardkit

# Editor / OS metadata.
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo

# Python virtualenvs and toolchain caches.
.venv
venv
env
.tox
.nox
.mypy_cache
.ruff_cache
.pytest_cache
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov
*.egg-info
build/
dist/

# Byte-compiled artefacts.
__pycache__
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd

# Source trees that the production image deliberately does NOT ship:
#   * tests/   — runtime image must not carry test code (image size, attack surface)
#   * docs/    — published docs site is separate
#   * tasks/   — GuardKit task-tracking markdown, never runtime input
#   * spikes/  — exploratory code, not production-ready
#   * features/ — Gherkin spec source, not runtime input
.dockerignore.local
tests/
docs/
tasks/
spikes/
features/

# Secrets & local environment overlays — defence in depth. The
# Dockerfile already refuses to COPY .env, but a stray `COPY . .` in a
# future stage must still be safe.
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
secrets/

# Docker / CI scratch.
Dockerfile.local
docker-compose*.yml
docker-compose*.yaml
.github/

# IDE/test reports.
*.log
coverage.xml
junit*.xml
